{
  "text": "Since {Q 1 , . . . , Q p } is linearly indendent it holds rank(Q) = p and, therefore, there exists a left inverse A ∈ R p×m 2 , i.e. AQ = I p . Multiplying both sides in [CITATION_1] with A from the left, we get ",
